post_text:
🎅🏽 Christmas In July 🎅🏽
A Downtown Ponchatoula InStore and Virtual Facebook Live Event

Tomorrow kicks off the start of Our Annual Christmas in July Event throughout our Downtown Businesses!

We’ve posted a Schedule Below 👇🏽👇🏽👇🏽
Make sure to follow all of these business on their Facebook pages to stream the Live videos!

⭐️ A Few Things To Remember For Tomorrow ⭐️

🔹 Businesses will be open to the public for walk in sales.
🔹Some Businesses May require a mask before entering.
🔹InStore Sales and Promotions will be offered.

🔹For those who are uncomfortable, or rather shop from home, each business listed is offering a Facebook Live Stream on their business pages.

🔹The Facebook Live Stream will allow customers to reach these stores virtually, and allow you to view items in real time from home!
🔹Call or Message these business to order, or curbside pickup if offered!
🔹Follow each business to watch their Live Videos!

We hope to see everyone out tomorrow or virtually! 🍓

Have fun, enjoy the weekend, and come to Downtown Ponchatoula!

post_text:
🎅🏽🍓 Christmas In July 🍓🎅🏽
A Downtown Business Event and Facebook Live Stream.

It’s Twelve Days Till Christmas In July!
During these twelve days leading up to the event, we will be promoting our downtown businesses, sales, specials, and more.

Downtown Businesses will be going live the entire day of this event showcasing their businesses, items, and everything they have to offer. Make sure to tune in the day of, July 25th, to virtually shop, browse, or to say hello on the Facebook Live Stream on each businesses Facebook page.

🍓Follow these businesses on Facebook to watch the Live Stream the day of Christmas in July!

🎅🏽 The Big Day Is Tomorrow!!!! 🎅🏽

Our last Facebook Live Participant of Christmas In July is Smay’s in Downtown Ponchatoula!

This is a great locally owned Restaurant with some great tasting food! 😊

They serve breakfast, lunch, and dinner, and believe me, you don’t want to skip a meal when eating at this little hot spot! The Foods That Good!!! 👍🏽

Smay’s will go Facebook Live beginning at 9:45 am tomorrow morning! Stay tuned!

post_text:
The Ponchatoula Chamber of Commerce is happy to announce that we have our permit and the Ponchatoula Chamber of Commerce Senior parade is a go!!!! The event will be held June 20th at 10:00a. We will start at the Lions Club, go down Pine Street, take a left at CVS, and end at Kiwanis Park. Contact the Ponchatoula Chamber office for a form that MUST be filled out by June 17th and returned to the Chamber office in order to participate. Please make note that the driver must have an attached copy of their drivers license and insurance info. If you have any questions or to obtain the form electronically, feel free to call the office 985-386-2536 or email chamber@ponchatoulachamber.com.
We are very much looking forward to this event and hope you stay in town all day to browse our shops, check out the car show, and enjoy the band that starts at 7p outside of Le Fleur De Lis Reception Hall and Catering.

post_text: While we are saddened that the current stay at home order has been extended to May 15, we are excited that phase 1 of the re-opening plans may be implemented in the near future. If your business is currently closed, please be sure to review the Governor’s current order and operate accordingly. In some cases, business can operate so long as there are no more than 10 individuals in the place of business and those in the building are wearing a mask. In other cases, curbside operations are possible. If you have not reviewed the SBA opportunities that have been provided, please do so at www.sba.gov. Know that that Ponchatoula Chamber of Commerce desire to be of assistance to you, any way we can. We look forward to the Governor’s address on May 11 as we anticipate further updates as to the state’s plans to reopen.

Once again, our community comes together to provide meals for essential personnel at North Oaks Hospital, this time being 400 meals to the night shift! This is a time to show our appreciation, and to show what our community is about. Coming together and working as a team to support those hard at work, that keep us safe, healthy, and well.

Meals were also delivered to Ponchatoula Police Department, Ponchatoula Vol. Fire Dept, Hammond Fire Dept and Acadian Ambulance.

We, the Chamber members of Ponchatoula, appreciate all of our local essential workers, especially those on the front line! We thank you all very much for all that you do.

Huge Thanks to:
Stray Cats Ponchatoula
Le Fleur De Lis Reception Hall and Catering
Stinky Mud Photography
Pat Farris for 7th Ward Marshal
Elmer's Chocolate Factory
The Ponchatoula Jaycees

🚨LABEOC Daily Update 🚨

- By April 17, U.S. citizens will be able to track the date their COVID-19 relief payment is scheduled to be deposited into their bank account using the IRS' new "Get My Payment" tool ➡️ https://buff.ly/2Xx0Fyn

- Governor John Bel Edwards announced that Louisiana is expected to receive $1.8B in aid within the next ten days. According to the governor, approximately 45% will go to local governments to help with virus response, while the rest would remain with state government.

- The June 20 Presidential Primary Election will be rescheduled for July 11, and the July 25 Municipal General Election is rescheduled to August 15. More information will be forthcoming from the Secretary of State.

-FEMA released the "Disaster Financial Management Guide" to support jurisdictions in establishing and implementing sound disaster financial management practices ➡️ https://buff.ly/3a643CY

Today, the Ponchatoula Chamber along with Stray Cats Ponchatoula, Stinky Mud Photography, and Le Fleur De Lis Reception Hall and Catering donated 1000 lunches to our health care workers at North Oaks. We were joined by The Ponchatoula Jaycees and fellow chamber members in helping us box up lunches.
We want to thank each and every front line worker for all they are doing in our hospitals and also the volunteers that came to help this morning.
If you would like to learn how to become a volunteer for the chamber and it’s events, please contact us! Volunteer work is the most rewarding work there is.
Keep supporting our healthcare workers by continuing social distancing and washing hands.
North Oaks Health System

*****edit: we are no longer accepting request for this Sunday. Please stay tuned for more dates in the near future. Thank you!!!!*****

We want to give to our community at this time.

✨🙏🏼He is not here. For he has risen, just as he said.🙏🏼✨

This Easter Sunday, we are driving around with our cameras and offering front porch family ‘porch’traits. If you live in Ponchatoula, please send us your address and we will give you a time that we will be in your area. All photos will be uploaded to an online digital gallery and free to download.

If all goes well, we may choose other dates, locations and maybe incorporate a pledging system, to give back to our local business’.

Edit: we will respect the social distancing order. Our zoom lenses will allow us to capture your picture from a good safe distance. We ask that you respect the order as well. This is not an opportunity for large group photos. Please keep it to the people who live in your house only. Thank you.

post_text:
If you own a small business that's been affected by Covid 19 and are trying to get an SBA loan, your local bank will able to facilitate that loan for you. It is called a 7A forgivable loan. If you use it for payroll, mortage/rent payment, utilities, etc, you will not be required to pay it back. Local banks start taking applications on Friday, April 3rd. If you would like additional information, go to Scalise.house.gov
Congressman Steve Scalise has just added information to his website. Click on the red banner at the top of the page. Scroll down to information for small businesses and there are links for lenders, borrowers, and the application can be found there. I’m sure it will make the process a lot smoother if you have the necessary information ready when you contact your bank.￼￼￼￼

When the Corona Virus finally exhausts itself and the danger is over, let's do something good for our country.

Let's spend our vacations in the USA, eat in local restaurants, buy American products, buy local meats and veggies, and support local businesses.

These businesses are going to find it very difficult to get back on their feet and survive without our help. They're suffering badly now.
Our products are some of the best in the world.
This country is one of the most beautiful. 🇺🇸🇺🇸 🇺🇸
Thank you Ginny Wilson for sharing this!

shared_text:
Ryan Helg
March 7 at 8:19 PM ·

Today was a fantastic day for Ponchatoula, Louisiana. I was swamped at my booth, but I managed to take a few moments to fly the drone up and grab a few aerial shots for the Ponchatoula Chamber of Commerce. Judy Vice Berner does a great job at organizing this event. I'm very proud to be a part of Antique Trade Days, and a director on the board. I love my city, and I hope to continue to be a part of bringing family friendly events such as this one to keep our city great! Don't worry, if you missed out today, we'll be out there again tomorrow with more beautiful weather. Come by and see us.
